Make sure you wash your hands right.
We all know that you have to wash them (e.g. when you come home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it the right way.
This is especially important now that the autumn infections are coming.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for the washing to remove the dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands.
Yet most of us wash them less.
Just warm water and simple soap - it is not true that it has to be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
By washing, we rub not only the underpants and the tops of the hands, but also: the tips of the fingers (joined or individually) - rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, the spaces between the fingers (interweave your hands, rubbing your fingers against each other), thumbs - each thumb embraces the other hand and in such a embrace we spin it a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when you cannot wash your hands) we should wipe your hands with a wet handkerchief and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the handle or the door (the recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate) with your hands washed.
Open them through the paper towel.
The Iranian President says he rejected the proposal to talk to the US, Donald Trump denies it.
Tehran did not engage with the US at the United Nations General Assembly in New York, despite the American offer to lift sanctions, "said Iranian President Hasan Rowhani on Friday.
The President of the United States, Donald Trump, commented that it was the Iranian party that asked for the removal of the restrictions, which he refused.
According to Iranian President Hasan Rowhani, the Americans have proposed the abolition of all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiations on a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear programme and the ballistic missile programme.
Rowhani: Iran will not engage in talks in the atmosphere of maximum pressure
The President of Iran has stated that he has refused to engage in these talks because of the 'toxic atmosphere'.
He stated that he had met with American diplomats because he had given in to the orders of France, Germany and the United Kingdom.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in the atmosphere of 'maximum pressure'.
"And even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in 5 + 1 format, no one can predict what the final result will be," said Rowhani.
The day before, the Iranian leader said that he did not rule out talks with the US and that the European parties to the nuclear agreement accused the American sanctions on Iran.
He added that sanctions imposed on Iran following the US withdrawal from the nuclear agreement "are a prerequisite that does not allow" for dialogue.
If we can lift this precondition and if America can lift sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America, "he declared.
He added that he did not exclude a meeting with the President of the United States Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation during the United Nations General Assembly during the past week.
Trump: "Iran asked, I said no"
Donald Trump tweeted that he rejected the Iranian request.
"Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said no to the president of the United States.
Voltage with atomic agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tensions between Washington and Tehran in some form to save the 2015 Iran agreement, which they were signatories to.
It stated that, in exchange for the abolition of economic sanctions, Iran would abandon its nuclear weapons programme and that the nuclear sector would be placed under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the US from the agreement in May 2015, the other signatories have often confirmed that they want to maintain the agreement in force.
It hasn't worked out yet.
Washington is using the tactics of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive an export licence for the raw material, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
